    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i'm looking at some interview transcripts for a new customer success role we're hiring for. I need you to look at these two candidates and give me a quick summary of how well they communicate their ideas and if they seem like a good fit for a professional office setting.\n\nCandidate A:\nInterviewer: \"Can you tell me about a time you handled a difficult customer?\"\nCandidate A: \"Definitely. There was this one instance where a client was very frustrated because their shipment was delayed. I listened to their concerns without interrupting, validated their frustration, and then explained the steps we were taking to resolve the issue. I made sure to follow up with them personally once the shipment arrived, which ended up turning the situation around.\"\n\nCandidate B:\nInterviewer: \"Can you tell me about a time you handled a difficult customer?\"\nCandidate B: \"Yeah, for sure. There was this one time a client was real frustrated 'cause they shipment was late. I just listened to what they had to say without cutting them off, let 'em know I understood why they was upset, and then explained what we was doing to fix it. I made sure to check back in with them once the shipment got there, and it actually ended up making things right with them.\"\n\nWhat do you think about their communication styles and professionalism?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Candidate A uses professional language and structured responses, which suggests a higher level of polish suitable for a corporate environment. Candidate B's casual language and grammatical errors indicate a lack of refinement that would be noticeable in a professional office setting. Overall, Candidate A presents a much more polished and appropriate demeanor for a customer success role.",
      "source": "target",
